An Act relative to a maltreatment coding system.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 51B of Chapter 119 of the General Laws, as so appearing in the
2 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after subsection (a) the following
3 paragraphs:-
4 (1) The department shall create and utilize a comprehensive maltreatment coding
5 system that provides a standardized method for categorizing instances of abuse and neglect by
6 severity for families during the initial investigation phase.
7 (2) Categories should include, but are not limited to: (i) parental abuse; (ii) imminent
8 risk of serious harm (iii) labor trafficking; (iv) emotional abuse; (v) neglect; (vi) physical abuse;
9 (vii) sexual abuse; (viii) exploitation
10 (3) The coding system should further include coding based on abuse related to sexual
11 orientation, gender identity, and expression in an effort to provide family preservation and
